**who —** The World Tree — the giant Yggdrasil-like tree that IS the entire game world — climbed branch by branch, holding the towns, the Elf and Dwarf realms, the three springs, and the high boughs where the Evil One waits

**what —** the giant Yggdrasil-like tree that IS the entire game world — climbed branch by branch, holding the towns, the Elf and Dwarf realms, the three springs, and the high boughs where the Evil One waits

**where —** FAX · Faxanadu — Hudson Soft, NES 1989 (Famicom 1987; Falcom's Xanadu line)  Framework inputs: Faxanadu; the World Tree; Eolis; the Mantras; the card-keys; Golds & Ranks  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** It is the stage as a living thing: a world you do not cross but climb, a tree dying from a poison at its root and a horror at its crown.

**how —** Crystallized from Faxanadu (NES 1989) — Famicom Xanadu, on Falcom's licensed Xanadu name.

**◌ the mythos —** It is the stage as a living thing: a world you do not cross but climb, a tree dying from a poison at its root and a horror at its crown. a being of the World Tree and the climb to the Evil One

